    <h1 class="text-center">.NET Migrations: Your First Database Changes</h1>
    
    <div class="beginner-explanation">
        <div class="beginner-explanation-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-database"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="beginner-explanation-content">
            <h3>What Are Migrations?</h3>
            <p><strong>Migrations are like "change instructions" for your database.</strong> When you update your C# code (like adding a new field to a user), migrations tell your database how to update itself to match.</p>
            
            <div class="simple-analogy">
                <div class="analogy-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-home"></i>
                    <div class="analogy-content">
                        <h5>Think of it like renovating a house:</h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Your C# code</strong> = The architect's blueprint</li>
                            <li><strong>Your database</strong> = The actual house</li>
                            <li><strong>Migrations</strong> = The contractor who updates the house to match the blueprint</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="important-note">
        <h4>Remember: Why We Need Migrations</h4>
        <p><strong>Without migrations</strong>, you'd have to manually update your database every time you change your code. <strong>With migrations</strong>, .NET does it automatically and keeps track of all changes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="migration-types">
        <h2>The Migration Process in 3 Steps</h2>
        
        <div class="types-grid">
            <div class="type-card">
                <div class="type-header">
                    <h4>1. Change Your Code</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="type-content">
                    <p><strong>Add/remove properties in your C# classes</strong></p>
                    <div class="code-example">
                        <code>public string PhoneNumber { get; set; }</code>
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Edit your ApplicationUser class</li>
                        <li>Add properties you need</li>
                        <li>Remove properties you don't need</li>
                        <li>Change property types if needed</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="type-card">
                <div class="type-header">
                    <h4>2. Create Migration</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="type-content">
                    <p><strong>Generate the migration file</strong></p>
                    <div class="code-example">
                        <code>Add-Migration AddPhoneNumber</code>
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Open Package Manager Console</li>
                        <li>Run Add-Migration command</li>
                        <li>Give it a descriptive name</li>
                        <li>Creates migration files automatically</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="type-card">
                <div class="type-header">
                    <h4>3. Update Database</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="type-content">
                    <p><strong>Apply changes to your database</strong></p>
                    <div class="code-example">
                        <code>Update-Database</code>
                    </div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Run Update-Database command</li>
                        <li>Applies all pending migrations</li>
                        <li>Updates database structure</li>
                        <li>Keeps your existing data safe</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="implementation-examples">
        <h2>Step-by-Step: Your First Migration</h2>
        
        <div class="examples-section">
            <div class="example">
                <h4>Adding First Name & Last Name to Users</h4>
                <p>Follow these exact steps to add new fields to your users:</p>
                
                <div class="example-tabs">
                    <button class="example-tab active" data-target="step1">Step 1: Edit Code</button>
