    </div>

    <div class="practical-tips">
        <h2>Migration Best Practices</h2>
        
        <div class="tips-grid">
            <div class="tip">
                <h4>Use Descriptive Names</h4>
                <p>Name migrations clearly: <code>AddPhoneNumber</code>, <code>RemoveOldEmail</code>, <code>CreateProductsTable</code>. This helps you remember what each migration does.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tip">
                <h4>One Change Per Migration</h4>
                <p>When learning, make one change at a time. Add one field, create migration, update database. This makes debugging easier.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tip">
                <h4>Test After Each Migration</h4>
                <p>After running <code>Update-Database</code>, always run your application to make sure it still works.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tip">
                <h4>Keep Migration Files</h4>
                <p>Don't delete migration files from your Migrations folder. They track your database history.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tip">
                <h4>Backup Your Database</h4>
                <p>Before major changes, make a backup of your database. Just in case!</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tip">
                <h4>Check for Errors</h4>
                <p>If <code>Add-Migration</code> fails, fix any red errors in your code first, then try again.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="common-patterns">
