        <div class="problems">
            <div class="problem">
                <h5>Problem: "No database provider has been configured"</h5>
                <div class="solution">
                    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> Make sure your <code>Program.cs</code> has database configuration:</p>
                    <div class="code-snippet-small">
                        <code>builder.Services.AddDbContext&lt;ApplicationDbContext&gt;(options =&gt;<br>    options.UseSqlServer(connectionString));</code>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="problem">
                <h5>Problem: Can't find Package Manager Console</h5>
                <div class="solution">
                    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> In Visual Studio: View → Other Windows → Package Manager Console</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="problem">
                <h5>Problem: "Build failed" when adding migration</h5>
                <div class="solution">
                    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> Fix any red errors in your C# code first. Build your project (Ctrl+Shift+B), then try again.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="problem">
                <h5>Problem: "Migration already exists"</h5>
                <div class="solution">
                    <p><strong>Fix:</strong> Give your migration a different name, or delete the old migration files first.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

